Meet <b>Pheebs2U</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Pheebs2U lives at <a href='/home/?user=pheebs2u'>19510 Wild Rose Road</a> in the beautiful, historical neighborhood of Ravenwood.  She has only been a citizen since March 13, 2005, but is already making quite an impression on her fellow citizens.<br><br>Her teachers at Millsberry Academy describe Pheebs2U as a very deep thinker.  Whether she's working on a complex math problem or a historical essay, you're sure to see Pheebs2U dedicatedly applying her mind to it.  Along with enabling her to excel in school, Pheebs2U's sharp intellect has already earned her a shiny gold trophy in Solver.<br><br>Because of her compassionate nature, Pheebs2U is always more than happy to help anyone who needs assistance, whether it's with some homework or a problem with their computer.  She's very interested in computers, and always welcomes the chance to either learn more or share some of her knowledge about them.<br><br>At home, Pheebs2U often works on her own computer, looking up information about two of her other greatest interests, mysteries and archaeology.  Quiet weekends will often find Pheebs2U up in her tree house, listening to some quiet country, classical, or pop music while devouring a suspenseful mystery book.  Oftentimes, her creative mind will even think up some mysteries of her own to write down.  <br><br>With regard to her other love, archaeology, Pheebs2U often sets aside several hours a week for reading up on all the latest archaeological finds.  When she and her friends are feeling adventurous, they like to go on "archeological digs."  During these "digs," Pheebs2U and her friends will explore the attics and basements belonging to some of Ravenwood's oldest homes.  The homes' owners always give Pheebs2U and her friends a warm welcome, since they make a great effort to leave everything neat and uncluttered after their "excavation," plus they've built a reputation for turning up long lost antiques that are often valuable.<br><br>On some of their more relaxing days, Pheebs2U and her friends like to hang out at the movie theater or Peabody Park (which she helps to keep clean).  If you'd like to swing by and say hello, Pheebs2U will usually be the one sporting green, red, or dark blue, since those are her favorite colors.  She loves to meet new people, so why not stop over and introduce yourself!<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Pheebs2U, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
